law.text:
A proceeding for judicial probate shall be instituted at any time before administrative probate or within the period after administrative probate provided by § 5-304 of this title.
At the request of an interested person;
By a creditor in the event that there has been no administrative probate;
If it appears to the court or the register that the petition for administrative probate is materially incomplete or incorrect in any respect;
If the will has been torn, mutilated, burned in part, or marked in a way as to make a significant change in the meaning of the will;
If it is alleged that a will is lost or destroyed.
